# SQLite Databases (if you don't want to commit local dev dbs)
# ---------------
# If your SQLite database is stored in a specific location you don't want committed.
# For example, if it's directly in backend/ or frontend/ for local dev.
# However, if it's inside a 'data' volume managed by Docker, this might not be necessary
# for the gitignore itself, but ensure the volume is not part of the image.
# backend/dev.db
# backend/data/*.db

# Specific to Create React App (if you ever used it or its remnants)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# build/

# TypeScript
# ----------
# *.tsbuildinfo # TypeScript incremental build information

# Test Runner Specific
# --------------------
# .jest-cache/

# Other
# -----
# Any other project-specific files or directories to ignore
# For example, if you generate documentation locally:
# docs/_build/

# Docker (usually you want to commit Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml)
# If you have local Docker volumes or caches you want to ignore from git
